track_notes: Hike begins in Granite Mountain Hotshots Memorial Park, an AZ State Park with free entry. Parking is very limited and they encourage using the shuttle from the fire station in nearby Yarnell. The first few miles follow the Hotshots memorial trail which commemorates the tragedy where 19 firefighters died. Plaques along the way tell about each and many people leave trinkets.  About 3 miles in, you reach a trail that goes down to the actual spot where they perished, with a large circular shrine of 19 large rock obelisks. It is an emotional hike whether you go down to the shrine or not.  At this point, you can enter AZ State Trust Land (permit required) and continue straight on an old trail that is more rugged, but not hard to follow.  This is prime snake habitat so I put on the snake gaitors. Also I saw plenty of evidence of wildcats.  A very nice hike with only a mild tenth of a mile bushwhack in the final ascent.  Top is rocky and awesome views for miles.
track_title: 6100 Peak via Granite Mountain Hotshots Memorial Trail
